Typically I don’t share much personal stuff here, but 2023 was one of the wildest years yet for me. Here’s some of my most popular work from this year and a rare photo of my ugly mug. 
.
First and foremost, I became a father in August and let me just say - it’s been the most mind bending experience of my life. Not surprisingly: it’s been stressful, but I’m very excited to continue helping this baby grow into a fully fledged human being. Or maybe even something cooler like a robot or a monster truck or something. 
.
It was also a record year for @holysmokes ! We did our first pop-up and released more new products than ever. Learning to juggle all of my life changes along with running the business has proved to be a bit of a challenge, but I’m looking forward to trying to top myself yet again in the new year. I’ve got some really fun stuff planned that I can’t wait to share. 
.
If you made it this far into this self indulgent rant, you’re a real one. I continue to be blown away by all of the support for my work and wouldn’t be able to continue doing this without  all of y’all. Thank you, sincerely, to everyone that continues to support me - both here and over @holysmokes . Being able to create for a living is not always easy, but I’m grateful for every moment of it. 🙏
